        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-6895",
        "content": "Three nights since when it was pretty late, and the moon very splendid, I saw her passing homewards close to the lake, and shouted down to her, meaning to say 'Good night'; but she thought that I had called her, and came: and sitting out on the top step we talked for hours, she without the yashmak.",
